cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.DS 

This paper deals with analyzing texts and finding unique fingerprints for them, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the possibility of exploiting hierarchical structures in the data, which is related to machine learning and data mining, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques to analyze the texts, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another possible sub-category. The use of ultrametric topology and tree structures also suggests that the paper may fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
